title: For Sale:  Spanish Mauser model 1916 in 308 / 7.62x51
postcontent: Solid old rifle, was purchased by previous owner as a deer rifle for his son, they fired it and wanted to keep it, but apparently they wanted a car chassis I had more, so we worked a trade and I don't really need this thing right now. Has been rechambered to fire .308 or 7.62x51 NATO rounds, very common to see on these, OT- serial number, from what I read that means 50,000 made of these total. Looks like it has been fired some, but bore looks pretty good and everything seems to cycle alright with .308 ammo. Numbers match except magwell floorplate, didn't see any numbers on the stock anywhere. One crack in upper handguard, but it still does the job, could be glued easily. Nice looking rifle in pretty good shape for the age, shows normal wear/tear, but nothing I noted bad aside from the upper handguard crack. I couldn't find hardly any Spanish Mausers with the double crossbolt setup through the stock like this one has, may be of more interest to someone because of this. No crest or other markings besides the OT- serial numbers.  Will consider trades, I'd say a trade value of around $175 on this.

As popular as this rifle is, it can be difficult to scope. The fixed integral scope bases limit the type of scopes that can be mounted.  A long scope with a smaller objective lens works best unless high Ruger rings are used.  The top hand guard interferes with large objective lenses and shorter scopes cannot be moved back far enough to obtain the proper eye relief.

A long tactical or varmint scope can be “bulky” on this compact rifle, so we tried mounting a mini-scope.  Our solution was to use an extended Picatinny rail adaptor that attaches to the fixed receiver bases and mount the scope using heavy duty Weaver style tactical rings. 
The mil-dot reticle is helpful in estimating the range to your target and the smaller scope profile makes it easier to handle your Rancher in the field or fit it into a scabbard or gun case.

SCOPE SPECIFICATIONS:
+ Magnification: 3x to 9x Wide Angle Variable Power
+ Objective Lens: 40mm
+ One Inch Tube
+ Weight: 10.3 Ounces
+ Length: 7.30 inches
+ Reticle: P4 Sniper with Range Estimating Mil-Dots
+ Eye Relief – 3 inches
+ Matte Black Finish
+ Windage & Elevation: 1/4" @100 Yards with Finger Adjust Knobs
+ Multi-Coated Lenses
+ Bright Optics
+ Sharp Focusing
+ Eye Piece Focus Lock Ring
+ Nitrogen Filled - Fog and Water Proof
+ Shock Proof – Heavy Duty Recoil Design
+ See-Thru Protective Lens Caps Included
+ New in Box
+ Limited Lifetime Warranty **

Picatinny Rail Mount Specifications
+ New design black anodized one piece aluminum Picatinny rail.
+ Mount dimensions are 7 inches long and ¾ inch wide. 
+ Four clamps lock into the receiver bases for a secure mounting platform.
+ Accepts all Weaver style rings with 5/8* wide clamps.

Rings Specifications

+ Heavy duty, non-slip aluminum construction with four allen head cap screws in each ring.
+ Matte Black Finish
+ Medium Height - Distance from top of receiver to center of rings is 1 inch. 
+ Rings are 5/8" thick and will accept 1 inch or 30mm tube diameter scopes.
+ Fits Standard Weaver and Picatinny Rail Bases
+ Allen head wrench included.

Mount and Rings Warranty: If mount or rings are defective in materials or workmanship, return them within ninety days and we will send you new ones.

This sale is for one 3~9x40 matte black mini-scope, one Picatinny rail scope mount for a Ruger Ranch Model semi-automatic rifle and one pair of heavy duty matte black one inch Weaver style scope rings. Rifles and other accessories shown in photos are not included.  NOT available in matte silver or stainless steel finish. 

Shipping available - or pick up in East Monument
